race.description: New Era Technology Country Boosted Handicap
race.comment: MOVE SHE CAN (7) improving mare who loomed strongly on resumption before her condition gave out late when a sound second over 1005m at Taree. Jumps in trip from the good gate and should prove too good for these. ENNIROC (5) deep into his preparation and the last two runs in Highway grade have been solid. Chipped away late when seventh to Shenandoah River over 1100m at Rosehill in a strong rating contest. Leading contender. ENSIGN PARKER (2) is starting to hit his straps and is undefeated in two attempts at this course. Just over a month between runs when surging late for a game third over 1100m at Wodonga. Winning apprentice hops back on and gets every opportunity from the barrier. OUTTA DE LADY (6) country-trained gelding going better than his recent runs suggest. On the quick backup after being anchored with the 60.5kg when sixth over 1100m at Armidale. Maps well and can take a hand in the finish.
